Khartoum â€” The Turkish Foreign Minister, Mouloud Gawishoglu, has affirmed the concern of Turkey with the security in Africa in general and in Sudan particularly. At a joint press conference with the Foreign Minister, Prof. Ibrahim Ghandour, the Turkish Foreign Minister said that Turkey will continue its support to Sudan in the fields of security and the combating of terrorism in the Red Sea area. He referred to a directives of the two presidents to provide security and police support to Sudan, affirming that the relations between Sudan and Turkey will be strengthened in the field of defence industry.